## Basics: Visualizing components

Selecting the `html` language option for a `code block` you can write **HTML** and **CSS classes** with **instant preview**

```html
  <template><button class="c-action t-primary">Sampled</button></template>
```

You can use available **components** too

```html
<template>
  <Selector :options="options" v-model="selection" />
  <div>Current selection: {{ selection }}</div>
</template>
<script>
({
  options: ['Option 1','Option 2','Option 3','Option 4'],
  selection: 'Option 3'
})
</script>
```

## Advanced: Prototyping web components

Selecting the `Webcomponent` language option for a `code block` you can prototype complete components using **HTML templates**, **Javascript** and **CSS rules** like a **SFC** with **instant preview**

```webcomponent
<template>
  <div class="example">{{ text }}</div>
</template>

<script>
({
 data: {
   text: ''
 },
 mounted(){
   this.text = 'Write here your prototypes'
 }
})
</script>
<style>
.example {
  border: 1px dashed currentColor;
  padding: 6px;
  border-radius: 3px;
}
</style>
```

